            <title>[FLINK-8499] Kryo must not be child-first loaded</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-8499</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Kryo classes are part of Flink API and hence move between Flink&apos;s core (serializers) and the user-application (Avro-Kryo-utils).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Duplicating the kryo dependency through reversed classloading yields problems. If Kryo is in the user application jar, together with Avro, the following error happens:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(this seems a semi-bug in the JVM, because this should clearly be a &lt;tt&gt;ClassCastException&lt;/tt&gt;, not such a cryptic byte code error).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
